Telangana TDP leaders on Sunday lashed out at the ruling TRS party saying its gimmicks would not work in the coming GHMC elections and the people would teach a befitting lesson.At a press conference here, TDP leaders Errabelli Dayakar Rao, Ravula Chandrasekhar Reddy and Vivek Goud said the Cabinet meeting held on Saturday confined itself to discussing ways to win GHMC elections instead of debating on farmersâ€™ problems, drought-hit mandals, farmers suicides, and drinking water shortage in villages. They also criticised laying of foundation stones for various projects without approvals and calling for tenders.